President Biden held a teleconference with mayors, governors, tribal and county leaders, and state and local officials to discuss the recently passed bipartisan infrastructure bill. He thanked them for their support and highlighted the importance of federal partnerships in solving infrastructure problems. The bill will create millions of jobs, invest in roads, bridges, clean energy, and clean water, and provide high-speed internet access. The President engaged in conversations with Governor Whitmer of Michigan, Mayor Dyer of Fresno, California, Commissioner Hausmann of Fulton County, and Principal Chief Hoskin of the Cherokee Nation in Oklahoma, discussing how the infrastructure bill will benefit their respective communities. The President emphasized the significance of the bill in improving the lives of all Americans and restoring faith in government. He also mentioned the importance of getting more people vaccinated to overcome the challenges posed by the Delta variant of COVID-19.